      textEn: [
        "My heart, don\u2019t pound so fiercely!\nDust, don\u2019t block my eyes!\nI grasp the yellow earth and won\u2019t let go,\nPressing it tight against my chest.\n\u2026Time and again I\u2019ve returned to Yan\u2019an in dreams,\nMy arms embracing Pagoda Hill.\nA thousand voices calling you \u2014\nMother Yan\u2019an, right here!",
        "Dufu River sings and Liulin village smiles,\nRed flags flutter, waving welcome.\nWhite sheepskin towels and red sashes \u2014\nDear ones cross the Yan River to greet us.\nSo many words, but none come out,\nI throw myself into the arms of my people\u2026",
        "\u2026Sent off at Twenty-Li, welcomed at Liulin,\nTen years apart and now home again.\nTreetops, branches, roots \u2014\nDear mountains, dear water, dear people.\nLambs nursing, eyes on their mothers \u2014\nMillet rice raised me to adulthood.",
        "Rice wine, oil cakes, charcoal fire,\nGathered in a circle on the kang.\nThe cave-dwelling packed so tight no wind gets through,\nStill footsteps sound on the hilltop above.",
        "A thousand legs and a thousand eyes\nStill not enough to walk and see!\nBlue sky like a great mirror overhead,\nYan\u2019an city shines in my heart.",
        "The red flag at Yangjialing flies high,\nRevolution surges ten thousand miles!\nFootprints beneath Pagoda Hill \u2014\nChairman Mao ascended Tiananmen!\nGrow wings and ride the clouds,\nReturn to Yan\u2019an to see our Mother!"
      ],
