      textEn: [
        "Only when there is a Bole in the world can there then be thousand-li horses. Thousand-li horses are common, but Boles are rare. Therefore, even a fine horse may be degraded in a groom\u2019s hands, die alongside ordinary horses in a stable, and never be recognized as a thousand-li horse.",
        "A horse that can run a thousand li may eat a whole dan of grain at one feeding. But those who feed it do not know it can run a thousand li. Though possessing thousand-li ability, without enough food its strength fails and its talent cannot show.",
        "They whip it without the proper method, feed it without bringing out its full ability, hear it neigh without understanding its meaning, then hold the whip and stand over it saying: \u2018There are no good horses in the world!\u2019 Alas! Are there truly no good horses? They truly do not know how to recognize horses!"
      ],
