      textEn: [
        "At dusk I lodged at Shihao village; an officer came seizing people at night. The old man fled over the wall; the old woman went out to answer. How furious the officer\u2019s shout! How bitter the woman\u2019s cry! I heard her step forward and speak: \u2018Three sons sent to Ye City garrison. One sent a letter home; two recently died in battle.\u2019",
        "In August, the autumn gales roar, rolling three layers of thatch from my roof. Oh, for a mansion of a thousand rooms to shelter all the cold scholars under heaven with joyful faces! Firm as a mountain against wind and rain. Alas! When shall I see such a building rise before me? Even if my own hut is destroyed and I freeze to death, that would be enough!",
        "The old charcoal seller cuts wood and burns charcoal in the southern hills. His face is covered with dust and ash, his temples grey, his ten fingers black. Pitiful \u2014 his clothes are thin, yet he worries charcoal is cheap and wishes for colder weather. Two riders come prancing \u2014 who are they? A yellow-robed palace envoy and his white-shirted attendant. Half a bolt of red gauze and a length of silk, tied to the ox\u2019s head as payment for the charcoal."
      ],
